thread.title: Prep Volleyball roundup

title: Prep Volleyball roundup
text:
Prep Volleyball roundup Herald Staff Report The Clinton Herald 
Morrison pulls out win at Erie 
ERIE, Ill. — Lauren Vos came up big on offense and defense, helping Morrison prevail for a 25-22, 17-25, 29-27 win against Erie on Thursday in Three Rivers Conference volleyball. 
Vos led the Fillies (15-9, 8-5 TRAC) in both kills (10) and digs (14). Brooke Stralow almost had a triple-double, finishing with nine kills, nine assists and 10 digs, while Emma Sitzmore had 19 assists and 14 digs. 
On the other side, Rachel Cobert led the Cardinals with 21 kills and 22 digs, and she also had three blocks and three aces. 
Prophets rally 
PROPHETSTOWN, Ill. — After dropping the first set, Prophets rebounded for to beat Peru St. Bede 18-25, 25-22, 25-22 on Thursday. 
Claire Milnes recorded 15 kills to lead the Prophets, and she also had a pair of ace serves. Maddie Fringer had 22 assists, and Jensyn McKinney registered 10 digs. 
Mohawks upended 
BELLEVUE — Fourth-seeded Midland upset host and top seed Marquette Catholic on Thursday in the pool-play portion of the Tri-Rivers Conference volleyball tournament. 
Marquette won its opener, 21-12, 21-4 over Cedar Valley Christian, getting three kills, two aces and six digs from Marissa Schroeder. 
Midland then beat Cedar Valley Christian 21-8, 21-14 before finishing the night by knocking off the hosts 21-19, 21-18. 
Erica Timmerman had eight kills to lead the Mohawks (18-6), and Teona Richman had seven kills and four blocks. 
Kortney Kirby had 20 assists for the night, while McKenna Hingtgen added 13. 
The conference tournament continues Saturday at Lisbon. 
In other conference tournament pool play Thursday, Calamus-Wheatland went 2-0 in its pool. The Warriors beat Prince of Peace 21-5, 21-9 and Easton Valley 22-20, 21-14. 
Maquoketa drops 2 
MOUNT VERNON — Maquoketa lost a pair of matches at the WaMaC Conference tournament. 
Center Point-Urbana defeated the Cardinals 21-9, 21-14, and Mount Vernon beat them 21-11, 21-5. Mount Vernon finished 3-0 on its home court. 
The losses dropped Maquoketa's record to 8-20. 
MORRISON 25-17-25, ERIE 21-25-27 
Statistical leaders 
Kills — Morrison (Lauren Vos 10, Brooke Stralow 9, Kassidee Church 8, Emma Sitzmore 5); Erie (Rachel Cobert 21, Emily Cox 7, Delaney Tegeler 5). Assists — Morrison (Sitzmore 19, Stralow 9, Allysa Criss 7); Erie (Cox 17, Cait Maloney 7). Digs — Morrison (Vos 14, Sitzmore 14, Stralow 10, Jordan Schmidt 9); Erie (Cobert 22, Maloney 18, Tegeler 17, Courtney Kruthoff 11. Blocks — Morrison (Stralow 1, Church 1, Vos 1); Erie (Cobert 3, Tegeler 2, Kruthoff 1). Aces — Morrison (Criss 2); Erie (Cobert 3, Kayla Mizlo 2).
